<p>I've defined a composite-id for my NHibernate database model. It seems to work, but I cannot set a generator for one key-property.</p>  <p>Is it possible to define a generator for a key-propery in a composite-id?</p>  <p><strong>C# NHibernate Model</strong></p>  <pre><code>public const string STR_ID = "Id"; public const string STR_SHARDKEY = "ShardKey";  [CompositeId(-4)] [KeyProperty(-3, Name = STR_ID, Column = STR_ID)] [KeyProperty(-2, Name = STR_SHARDKEY , Column = STR_SHARDKEY )] [Generator(-1, Class = "guid.comb")] public virtual Guid? Id { get; set; }  [Column(Name = STR_SHARDKEY )] public virtual int ShardKey{ get; set; } </code></pre>  <p><strong>XML Mapping</strong></p>  <pre class="lang-xml prettyprint-override"><code>&lt;composite-id&gt;     &lt;key-property name="Id" column="Id" /&gt;     &lt;key-property name="ShardKey" column="ShardKey" /&gt; &lt;/composite-id&gt; </code></pre>  <p>Shouldn't there be a generator tag like <code>&lt;generator class="guid.comb" /&gt;</code> somewhere? </p>